{{Coord|37|17|17.6|N|75|55|34.2|W|display=title}} 
The '''Anheuser–Busch Coastal Research Center''' is a biological field station located in [[Oyster, Virginia]] that is operated by the [[University of Virginia]]. It is a member of the [[Organization of Biological Field Stations]] (OBFS). It serves as the research home for the [[Virginia Coast Reserve Long-Term Ecological Research]] Program. A new $2.5 million laboratory and housing facility was dedicated in on August 26, 2006.<ref>{{cite news|first=Jacqueline |last=Minneman |title=University upgrades coastal research center |url=http://www.cavalierdaily.com/news/2006/aug/29/university-upgrades-coastal-research-center/ |archive-url=https://archive.is/20120721091220/http://www.cavalierdaily.com/news/2006/aug/29/university-upgrades-coastal-research-center/ |dead-url=yes |archive-date=2012-07-21 |format= |work=[[The Cavalier Daily]] |date=2006-08-29 |accessdate=2007-11-17 }}</ref>

The Center is located within the [[Virginia Coast Reserve]], a [[biosphere reserve]] operated by the [[Nature Conservancy]].

