{{Infobox dam | name = Moglicë Hydro Power Plant | name_official = | image = | image_size = | image_caption = | image_alt = | location_map = Albania | location_map_size = | location_map_caption = | coordinates = {{coord|40.69|20.44|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | country = [[Albania]] | location = [[Moglicë]] | status = UC | construction_began = 2013 | opening = 2018 (est.) | demolished = | cost = | owner = [[Statkraft|Devoll Hydropower]] | dam_type = | dam_height = {{Convert|150|m|ft|abbr=on}} | dam_height_thalweg = | dam_height_foundation= | dam_length = {{Convert|320|m|ft|abbr=on}} | dam_width_crest = | dam_width_base = | dam_volume = | dam_elevation_crest = | dam_crosses = [[Devoll (river)|Devoll]] | spillway_count = | spillway_type = | spillway_capacity = | res_name = | res_capacity_total = {{Convert|360000000|m3|acre.ft|abbr=on}} | res_capacity_active = | res_capacity_inactive= | res_catchment = | res_surface = {{Convert|7.2|km2|mi2|abbr=on}} | res_elevation = | res_max_depth = | res_max_length = | res_max_width = | res_tidal_range = | plant_operator = | plant_commission = | plant_decommission = | plant_type = | plant_turbines = 2 x 90.2 MW [[Francis-type]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Devoll Hydropower (DHP), Albania|url=http://cdmloanscheme.org/sites/default/files/5577_pdd__devoll_hydropower_dhp_albania.pdf|publisher=UN-CDM|accessdate=14 August 2015}}</ref> | plant_hydraulic_head = {{Convert|300|m|ft|abbr=on}} | plant_capacity = 172&nbsp;[[Megawatt|MW]] | plant_annual_gen = 475 GWh est. | website = | extra = }} '''Moglicë Hydro Power Plant''' is a large [[hydroelectricity]] plant under construction on the river [[Devoll (river)|Devoll]] situated near the village [[Moglicë]], [[Albania]]. The project consists of a large power plant with an installed capacity of 172 MW and an average annual production of 475 GWh.<ref>[http://www.devollhydropower.al/new/?page_id=7441 Devoll Hydropower]</ref> It is built by Devoll Hydropower, an Albanian company owned by Norwegian power company [[Statkraft]].<ref>{{Cite web|title = Statkraft buys EVN AG's share in Devoll hydropower project|url = http://www.hydroworld.com/articles/2013/03/statkraft-buys-evn-ag-s-share-in-devoll-hydropower-project.html|website = www.hydroworld.com|accessdate = 2015-11-03}}</ref> The asphalt-core [[rock-fill dam]] will be 320 m long, 150 m high and 460 m wide.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Devoll Hydropower {{!}} F.A.Q|url = http://www.devollhydropower.al/new/?page_id=7754|website = www.devollhydropower.al|accessdate = 2015-11-03}}</ref> The dam is anticipated to be the world's highest of its kind upon completion.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Devoll Hydropower Project|url = http://www.power-technology.com/projects/devoll-hydropower-project/|website = Power Technology|accessdate = 2015-11-03}}</ref> The reservoir will have a surface area of 7.2&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup>, and a storage capacity of about 360 million m<sup>3</sup>. The power plant is part of the Devoll Hydropower Project and construction on it began in June 2013.<ref>{{cite web|title=Statkraft starts construction of Devoll hydropower plants in Albania|url=http://renewables.seenews.com/news/statkraft-starts-construction-of-devoll-hydropower-plants-in-albania-359845|publisher=SeeNews|accessdate=13 August 2015|date=17 June 2013}}</ref> It is expected to be completed in 2018.<ref>[http://www.statkraft.com/about-statkraft/Projects/albania/devoll/ Statkraft]</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = Statkraft to begin 278 MW Devoll hydropower project in Albania|url = http://www.pennenergy.com/articles/pennenergy/2013/06/statkraft--to-begin-243-mw-hydro-power-generation-project-in-alb.html|website = www.pennenergy.com|accessdate = 2015-11-03}}</ref>
