'''Pyridinium ''p''-toluenesulfonate''' ('''PPTS''') is a [[salt (chemistry)|salt]] of [[pyridine]] and [[p-Toluenesulfonic acid|''p''-toluenesulfonic acid]]. It is a colourless solid.
== Uses == In [[organic synthesis]], PPTS is used as a weakly acidic [[catalyst]], providing an organic soluble source of pyridinium (C<sub>5</sub>H<sub>5</sub>NH<sup>+</sup>) ions. For example, PPTS is used to deprotect [[silyl|silyl ethers]] or [[Tetrahydropyran|tetrahydropyranyl ethers]] when a substrate is unstable to stronger acid catalysts. It is also a commonly used catalyst for the preparation of [[Acetal|acetals]] and [[Ketal|ketals]] from aldehydes and ketones.
